content:
Thinking about it twice, I think that from a user standpoint, having the error message with the line of the last valid token is more user friendly. So, I will update my solution to change the approach, but I will also add a test with this crazy formatting.

There is also a last point which is not covered by tests and may be not clear in the goal. It is possible to reuse the same ident for var, const and procedure in sub levels.

var i;
procedure sub;
var i;
...

I propose to add a test/validator for this as well.

Please check out the following custom case:

15
const k=5, L=8;
var m;

PROCEDURE print;
! ( k -L +m ) ;

PROCEDURE run;
const m = 10;
VAR I, k;
? I;? k;WHILE -L <= I DO I := I / m * k;
! I;

m := 97;
call run;
call print.

I don't understand why there is an error of "Unknown variable".
